The paper deals with performance evaluation of parallel systems, which is a topic that falls under the purview of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.PF (Performance), which specifically deals with the analysis and optimization of computer system performance. The paper also deals with distributed computing (cs.DC), as it discusses the use of frameworks like MapReduce and Hadoop for parallelization. The paper also touches upon systems and control theory (cs.SY), as it uses queuing models to analyze the behavior of parallel systems. Additionally, the paper deals with networked systems (cs.NI), as it considers the effects of bursty arrivals on system performance. Finally, the paper deals with data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), as it discusses the use of Markov-additive processes to model the behavior of parallel systems.
